        <div subtype="part" type="section">
          <div type="section" subtype="case" n="C.19">
            <head>(C.19)</head>
            <div type="textpart" subtype="dictum" n="C.19 d.init.">
              <head>(C.19 d.init.)</head>
              <ab>Two clerics wanted to transfer to a monastery, and each sought
              permission from his bishop to do so. A question arises as to
              whether a bishop ought to permit a cleric to leave his own church
              behind and become a monk. If a bishop presented with such a
              request does not want to grant permission, a second question
              arises as to whether a cleric can enter a monastery even if his
              bishop is unwilling to permit it. Finally, does it make a
              difference if the clerics seeking permission to transfer to a
              monastery are canons regular instead of secular clergy? If so, a
              third question arises as to whether the clerics ought to be
              granted entry into a monastery even if they are canons
              regular.</ab>
            </div>
          </div>
